# Aorist Stems — Memory Drill

## Purpose

Drill present→aorist stem mapping for suppletive and irregular verbs. These forms cannot be derived from the present stem — they must be memorised cold.

Prompt format: present tense (English gloss) → aorist sg1
Example: "eat (τρώω) → ?" → "έφαγα"

## Why this belongs in memory drills

Regular aorist (-σα pattern: δουλεύω→δούλεψα) can be computed from the present stem and does not belong here. Suppletive and irregular stems are arbitrary mappings. The learning sequence explicitly flags these as "must be memorised."

## Phase 2 core set (Phase 2 prerequisite)

| Present | Aorist sg1 | Stem type |
|---------|------------|-----------|
| τρώω    | έφαγα      | suppletive |
| πίνω    | ήπια       | suppletive |
| βλέπω   | είδα       | suppletive |
| πηγαίνω / πάω | πήγα | suppletive |
| λέω     | είπα       | suppletive |
| έρχομαι | ήρθα       | suppletive |
| κάνω    | έκανα      | irregular -κα |
| παίρνω  | πήρα       | irregular |
| φεύγω   | έφυγα      | irregular |
| βρίσκω  | βρήκα      | irregular |
| δίνω    | έδωσα      | irregular |
| μαθαίνω | έμαθα      | irregular |
| γράφω   | έγραψα     | -ψα (predictable but worth drilling) |
| διαβάζω | διάβασα    | -σα (predictable but worth drilling) |
| αγοράζω | αγόρασα    | -σα (predictable but worth drilling) |

## Drill modes

**Forward**: Given English meaning + present form → produce aorist sg1
  - "eat (τρώω) → ?"  → "έφαγα"

**Reverse**: Given aorist sg1 → identify present / English meaning
  - "ήπια → ?"  → "πίνω / drink"

## Grouping suggestion

Allow user to filter by stem type:
- Suppletive only (hardest, highest priority)
- Irregular -κα/-γα
- All (full set)

## Time limits

Forward: 5 seconds (production under pressure)
Reverse: 4 seconds (recognition, slightly easier)

## Notes

- Drill as complete aorist sg1 forms, not "stems" — the augment is part of what must be recalled
- Do not mix regular -σα verbs into the suppletive-only filter
- Future forms (θα φάω, θα πιω) share the same stem — once aorist is learned, future comes almost free; note this in the post-session summary
